bash.sh
---------------------
Displays a random fortune from bash.org.pl 
Only in polish, sorry!

check_sap_chan.py
---------------------
A nagios script which checks if all SAP channels are online

check_snmp_switch_san.py
---------------------
A nagios script which checks the status of sensors and ports on a BROCADE FC switch

Based on a really ugly (yet educational) script by Roderick Derks (roderick@r71.nl)

check_tsm_drive.sh
---------------------
A nagios script which checks if all TSM drives are online
The monitoring machine must have dsmadmc installed

check_tsm_paths.sh
---------------------
A nagios script which checks if all TSM paths are online
The monitoring machine must have dsmadmc installed

check_tsm_tapes.py
---------------------
A nagios script which checks if you are running out of tapes in a TSM storage pool
The monitoring machine must have dsmadmc installed

cntlm_proxy.sh
---------------------
Source to use cntlm as a proxy

eth_status.sh
---------------------
Shows the status of a given wired interface. Useful for tools like xmobar or dzen

generate_readme.sh
---------------------
Generates a README file for the repository :-D

grabber.sh
---------------------
Takes a screenshot of a selected area and then displays it - useful for making fast memos, for example for interface configuration before changing it

grepkill.sh
---------------------
Shows a list of processes which match the given pattern and
then allows you to kill it

ishg.c
---------------------
Checks if the current directory is a mercurial repository
Works well (and speeds up considerably) with the "hg status" plugin

launch.sh
---------------------
This is a really handly little script that takes any simple command and runs it in the background. 
It logs all output into files in ~/.launch in a nice organized manner.

lock_unclutter.sh
---------------------
Allows using a screen locker with the awesome ,,unclutter'' utility

ntp_http.sh
---------------------
A very handy script to synchronize time through http headers when ntp is unavailable.
Works well through NTLM proxies with cntlm.

scrabble.sh
---------------------
Finds the words you can make from the given letters

sshcopyid.sh
---------------------
Copy an ssh key to a remote machine when ssh-copy-id is unavailable
or the service is running on a non-default port.

switch_mon.sh
---------------------
The script activates a monitor connected to the VGA port and
turns off the laptop LCD panel, changing the wallpaper afterwards

wlan_status.sh
---------------------
Shows the status of a given wireless interface. Useful for tools like xmobar or dzen

xrun.sh
---------------------
Opens an xterm window with the program given as an argument. Very nice for binding to a key things like alsamixer or htop, since the second run of the script closes the previously opened window

